items.title: Awesome Blazor
items.content_text:
### CMS

*   [BlazorShop (⭐320)](https://github.com/kalintsenkov/BlazorShop) - ![stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/kalintsenkov/BlazorShop?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=604800) ![Last commit](https://img.shields.io/github/last-commit/kalintsenkov/BlazorShop?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=86400) Simple shop application built with Blazor WebAssembly.
*   [FluentCMS (⭐481)](https://github.com/fluentcms/FluentCMS) - ![GitHub stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/fluentcms/FluentCMS?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=604800) ![GitHub stars](https://img.shields.io/github/last-commit/fluentcms/FluentCMS?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=86400) FluentCMS is open source AI Driven ASP.NET Core Blazor Content Management System (CMS) [FluentCMS](https://fluentcms.com/).

### Rapid Development Framework

*   [Oqtane (⭐2.1k)](https://github.com/oqtane/oqtane.framework) - ![GitHub stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/oqtane/oqtane.framework?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=604800) ![GitHub stars](https://img.shields.io/github/last-commit/oqtane/oqtane.framework?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=86400) Oqtane is a CMS & Application Framework for Blazor & .NET MAUI [Oqtane](https://www.oqtane.org).

### 2D/3D Rendering engines / JavaScript

*   [BlazorScriptReload (⭐21)](https://github.com/devessenceinc/BlazorScriptReload) - ![stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/devessenceinc/BlazorScriptReload?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=604800) ![last commit](https://img.shields.io/github/last-commit/devessenceinc/BlazorScriptReload?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=86400) A component which provides support for using JavaScript in Blazor Web Applications

### Articles / Others

*   [C# / Blazor Wolfenstein - Part 6 - The Basic Raycaster](https://www.jamesdrandall.com/posts/csharp_blazor_wolfenstein_part_6_the_basic_raycaster/) - September 18, 2022 - Part 6 of the articles explaining how port the game Wolfenstein 3D on C# and Blazor. [Source code (⭐76)](https://github.com/JamesRandall/csharp-wolfenstein) ![stars](https://img.shields.io/github/stars/JamesRandall/csharp-wolfenstein?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=604800) ![last commit](https://img.shields.io/github/last-commit/JamesRandall/csharp-wolfenstein?style=flat-square\&cacheSeconds=86400).

### Community / Others

*   [BuiltOnBlazor](https://builtonblazor.net) - A showcase of sites running on Blazor

items.title: Awesome Ios
items.content_text:
### UI

*   [AmazingBubbles (⭐64)](https://github.com/GlebRadchenko/AmazingBubbles) - Apple Music like Bubble Picker using Dynamic Animation.
*   [ApplyStyleKit (⭐209)](https://github.com/shindyu/ApplyStyleKit) - Elegant apply style, using Swift Method Chain.
*   [AZEmptyState (⭐85)](https://github.com/Minitour/AZEmptyState) - A UIControl subclass that makes it easy to create empty states.
*   [BAFluidView (⭐1.4k)](https://github.com/antiguab/BAFluidView) - UIView that simulates a 2D view of a fluid in motion.
*   [BackgroundVideoiOS (⭐562)](https://github.com/Guzlan/BackgroundVideoiOS) - A swift and objective-C object that lets you add a background video to iOS views.
*   [BatteryView (⭐51)](https://github.com/yonat/BatteryView) - Simple battery shaped UIView.
*   [BouncyPageViewController (⭐845)](https://github.com/BohdanOrlov/BouncyPageViewController) - Page view controller with bounce effect.
*   [Cacao (⭐1.1k)](https://github.com/PureSwift/Cacao) - Pure Swift Cross-platform UIKit (Cocoa Touch) implementation (Supports Linux).
*   [ClassicKit (⭐2.2k)](https://github.com/Baddaboo/ClassicKit) - A collection of classic-style UI components for iOS.
*   [ComponentKit](https://componentkit.org/) - A React-Inspired View Framework for iOS, by Facebook.
*   [ConfettiView (⭐234)](https://github.com/OrRon/ConfettiView) - Confetti View lets you create a magnificent confetti view in your app.
*   [DCKit (⭐141)](https://github.com/agordeev/DCKit) - Set of iOS controls, which have useful IBInspectable properties. Written on Swift.
*   [DistancePicker (⭐119)](https://github.com/qmathe/DistancePicker) - Custom control to select a distance with a pan gesture, written in Swift.
*   [DrawerKit (⭐782)](https://github.com/babylonhealth/DrawerKit) - DrawerKit lets an UIViewController modally present another UIViewController in a manner similar to the way Apple's Maps app works.
*   [ElongationPreview (⭐895)](https://github.com/Ramotion/elongation-preview) - ElongationPreview is an elegant push-pop style view controller with 3D-Touch support and gestures.
*   [FAQView (⭐474)](https://github.com/mukeshthawani/FAQView) - An easy to use FAQ view for iOS written in Swift.
*   [FlourishUI (⭐227)](https://github.com/thinkclay/FlourishUI) - A highly configurable and out-of-the-box-pretty UI library.
*   [FSPagerView (⭐7.3k)](https://github.com/WenchaoD/FSPagerView) - FSPagerView is an elegant Screen Slide Library. It is extremely helpful for making Banner, Product Show, Welcome/Guide Pages, Screen/ViewController Sliders.
*   [GDCheckbox (⭐26)](https://github.com/saeid/GDCheckbox) - An easy-to-use custom checkbox/radio button component for iOS, with support of IBDesign Inspector.
*   [GDGauge (⭐84)](https://github.com/saeid/GDGauge) - Full Customizable, Beautiful, Easy to use gauge view Edit.
*   [GaugeKit (⭐1k)](https://github.com/skywinder/GaugeKit) - Customizable gauges. Easy reproduce Apple's style gauges.
*   [HamsterUIKit (⭐31)](https://github.com/Howardw3/HamsterUIKit) - A simple and elegant UIKit(Chart) for iOS.
*   [Haptica (⭐790)](https://github.com/efremidze/Haptica) - Easy Haptic Feedback Generator.
*   [HorizontalDial (⭐214)](https://github.com/kciter/HorizontalDial) - A horizontal scroll dial like Instagram.
*   [IGColorPicker (⭐277)](https://github.com/iGenius-Srl/IGColorPicker) - A customizable color picker for iOS in Swift.
*   [JDFlipNumberView (⭐787)](https://github.com/calimarkus/JDFlipNumberView) - Representing analog flip numbers like airport/trainstation displays.
*   [KPActionSheet (⭐7)](https://github.com/khuong291/KPActionSheet) -  A replacement of default action sheet, but has very simple usage.
*   [LCUIComponents (⭐7)](https://github.com/linhcn/LCUIComponents) - A framework supports creating transient views on top of other content onscreen such as popover with a data list.
*   [LeeGo (⭐965)](https://github.com/wangshengjia/LeeGo) - Declarative, configurable & highly reusable UI development as making Lego bricks.
*   [Material (⭐12k)](https://github.com/CosmicMind/Material) - Material is an animation and graphics framework that allows developers to easily create beautiful applications.
*   [MEVHorizontalContacts (⭐357)](https://github.com/manuelescrig/MEVHorizontalContacts) - An iOS UICollectionViewLayout subclass to show a list of contacts with configurable expandable menu items.
*   [Mixin (⭐45)](https://github.com/oney/Mixin) - React.js like Mixin. More powerful Protocol-Oriented Programming.
*   [NightView (⭐162)](https://github.com/Boris-Em/NightView) - Dazzling Nights on iOS.
*   [NotchKit (⭐1.8k)](https://github.com/HarshilShah/NotchKit) - A simple way to hide the notch on the iPhone X
*   [NotchToolkit (⭐57)](https://github.com/AFathi/NotchToolkit) - A framework for iOS that allow developers use the iPhone X notch in creative ways.
*   [OAStackView (⭐2.1k)](https://github.com/nsomar/OAStackView) - OAStackView tries to port back the stackview to iOS 7+. OAStackView aims at replicating all the features in UIStackView.
*   [OverlayContainer (⭐1.2k)](https://github.com/applidium/OverlayContainer) - A library to develop overlay based interfaces, such as the one presented in the iOS 12 Apple Maps or Stocks apps.
*   [Overlay (⭐51)](https://github.com/TintPoint/Overlay) - Overlay is a flexible UI framework designed for Swift. It allows you to write CSS like Swift code.
*   [PageController (⭐408)](https://github.com/hirohisa/PageController) - Infinite paging controller, scrolling through contents and title bar scrolls with a delay.
*   [Pages (⭐496)](https://github.com/hyperoslo/Pages) - UIPageViewController made simple.
*   [Reactions (⭐583)](https://github.com/yannickl/Reactions) - Fully customizable Facebook reactions control.
*   [RKNotificationHub (⭐3k)](https://github.com/cwRichardKim/RKNotificationHub) - Make any UIView a full fledged notification center.
*   [SegmentedProgressBar (⭐473)](https://github.com/D-32/SegmentedProgressBar) - Snapchat / Instagram Stories style animated indicator.
*   [ShadowView (⭐416)](https://github.com/PierrePerrin/ShadowView) - Make shadows management easy on UIView.
*   [SCTrelloNavigation (⭐797)](https://github.com/SergioChan/SCTrelloNavigation) - An iOS native implementation of a Trello Animated Navigation.
*   [Splitflap (⭐1.1k)](https://github.com/yannickl/Splitflap) - A simple split-flap display for your Swift applications.
*   [STAControls (⭐12)](https://github.com/Stunner/STAControls) – Handy UIControl subclasses. (Think Three20/NimbusKit of UIControls.) Written in Objective-C.
